# Soft Delete — Mandatory (No Exceptions)

Read: `docs/09-development/SOFT-DELETE-POLICY.md`

## Absolute rules

- ❌ `prisma.*.delete()` / `deleteMany()` on business data — **FORBIDDEN**
- ✅ Soft delete only: `deletedAt`, `deletedById`, optional `deleteReason`
- ✅ Default queries: `deletedAt: null` — Prisma extension required
- ✅ Restore API for platform admin / tenant owner
- ✅ Audit log on soft delete + restore

## User visibility

Deleted data **invisible** to normal users — exists in DB for recovery.

## Exceptions (ephemeral only)

OTP Redis, rate limits, JWT TTL — not business entities.

## Never delete

AuditLog, OutboxEvent — append-only forever.

## Privacy (customer erasure)

Soft delete + pseudonymize — **not** hard delete. Financial records retained.

## CI

Reject PRs with Prisma `.delete(` on business models.

